'''Biopôle''' is a [[science park]] of 80,000 square metres destined to host companies whose main activity is in the life sciences field. While it is open to all therapeutic areas, the main focus is on developing innovative solutions in the fields of [[oncology]], [[immunology]] and [[Personalized medicine|personalised medicine]].<ref name=Boder/> Biopôle offers space for industrial [[research and development]] or administrative use.

The Biopôle is owned at 98% by the [[Canton of Vaud]].<ref name=Boder>{{fr}} Willy Boder, [https://www.letemps.ch/economie/2016/07/11/biopole-vaudois-se-relance "Le Biopôle vaudois se relance"], ''[[Le temps]]'', 11 July 2016 (page visited on 16 September 2016).</ref> It is located in [[Épalinges]], to the north of [[Lausanne]] and is the first of its kind in French-speaking part of [[Switzerland]]. The Biopôle site is located at the intersection of the large Lausanne campus, complementing the [[University Hospital of Lausanne|University Hospital of Lausanne (CHUV)]], the [[École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne|Swiss Federal Institute of Technology in Lausanne (EPFL)]], the [[University of Lausanne]] and the major industrial concerns.

