The '''convective temperature''' ('''CT''' or '''T<sub>c</sub>''') is the approximate [[temperature]] that [[air]] near the surface must reach for [[cloud]] formation without mechanical lift. In such case, [[cloud base]] begins at the [[convective condensation level]] (CCL), whilst with mechanical lifting, [[condensation]] begins at the [[lifted condensation level]] (LCL). Convective temperature is important to forecasting [[thunderstorm]] development.
