In [[particle physics]], a '''dijet event''' is a collision between [[subatomic particle]]s that produces two [[particle jet]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlas.ch/news/2011/search-for-new-physics-dijet-events.html |title=ATLAS Experiment |publisher=Atlas.ch |date=2011-06-21 |accessdate=2013-10-03}}</ref>

Dijet events are measured at [[LHC]] to constrain [[Quantum chromodynamics|QCD]] models, in particular the [[parton evolution equation]]s<ref>{{Cite journal|arxiv=1204.0696 |title=Ratios of dijet production cross sections as a function of the absolute difference in rapidity between jets in proton-proton collisions at sqrt(s) = 7 TeV |journal=The European Physical Journal C |volume=72 |issue=11 |date=2012 |last1=Collaboration |first1=CMS |last2=Khachatryan |first2=V. |last3=Sirunyan |first3=A. M. |last4=Tumasyan |first4=A. |last5=Adam |first5=W. |last6=Bergauer |first6=T. |last7=Dragicevic |first7=M. |last8=Erö |first8=J. |last9=Fabjan |first9=C. |last10=Friedl |first10=M. |last11=Frühwirth |first11=R. |last12=Ghete |first12=V. M. |last13=Hammer |first13=J. |last14=Hoch |first14=M. |last15=Hörmann |first15=N. |last16=Hrubec |first16=J. |last17=Jeitler |first17=M. |last18=Kiesenhofer |first18=W. |last19=Krammer |first19=M. |last20=Liko |first20=D. |last21=Mikulec |first21=I. |last22=Pernicka |first22=M. |last23=Rahbaran |first23=B. |last24=Rohringer |first24=C. |last25=Rohringer |first25=H. |last26=Schöfbeck |first26=R. |last27=Strauss |first27=J. |last28=Taurok |first28=A. |last29=Teischinger |first29=F. |last30=Wagner |first30=P. |doi=10.1140/epjc/s10052-012-2216-6 |display-authors=29 |bibcode = 2012EPJC...72.2216C }}</ref> and [[parton distribution functions]]. This is accomplished by measuring the [[azimuthal correlation]]s between the two jets.

